messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /consumer/budget

- all HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false

- POST: true

- OPTIONS: false

- TRACE: false

- GET: false

- PUT: false

- DELETE: false

- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The method handling this endpoint is calcBudgetForPrintRequest annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/consumer/budget", method = RequestMethod.POST). That explicitly maps only POST to the path "/consumer/budget".
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping or other shown prefix in the provided controller, so the full path is exactly "/consumer/budget".
- Only POST is explicitly allowed by the code. Per the instruction to base acceptability on the code (not runtime/server behavior), no other HTTP methods are acceptable because they are not declared on this mapping. In particular:
  - HEAD is not declared (and there is no GET mapping that would implicitly enable HEAD), so HEAD is false.
  - OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, GET, DELETE, PATCH are not declared and therefore are false.
- "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false because the mapping restricts to POST only.
